author: Michael Salfino
title: Dynasties Are Typically Great Ensembles—Except in New England - WSJ
text:
The Patriots dynasty has been long established irrespective of the outcome of Super Bowl LI. But it’s on track to be the oddest one in Super Bowl history. What makes this team unique is the lack of Hall of Fame players on at least two of these championship teams. It’s perhaps the ultimate testament to coach Bill Belichick and quarterback Tom Brady.
